**Segments**

- By Drug Type: Corticosteroids, Intravenous Immune Globulin, Thrombopoietin Receptor Agonists, Others
- By Distribution Channel: Hospital Pharmacies, Retail Pharmacies, Online Pharmacies

The Idiopathic Thrombocytopenic Purpura (ITP) or Immune Thrombocytopenic Purpura treatment drugs market can be segmented by drug type and distribution channel. In terms of drug type, the market is categorized into corticosteroids, intravenous immune globulin, thrombopoietin receptor agonists, and others. Corticosteroids are often used as first-line treatment to suppress the immune system's attack on platelets. Intravenous immune globulin is infused into the veins to help raise platelet counts. Thrombopoietin receptor agonists stimulate the bone marrow to produce more platelets. Other treatment options may include splenectomy, rituximab, and immunosuppressants. Regarding distribution channels, these drugs are typically made available through hospital pharmacies, retail pharmacies, and online pharmacies.

